President Obama announced his intent to nominate Luis C. de Baca as Ambassador-at-Large to Monitor and Combat Trafficking in Persons at the State Department. De Baca is currently Counsel to the U.S. House Committee on the Judiciary, on detail from the Civil Rights Division of the U.S. Department of Justice. He has experience in national security, intelligence, immigration, civil rights, and modern slavery issues. De Baca has investigated and prosecuted human trafficking cases involving various forms of exploitation. He has received recognition for his work in combating modern slavery, including the Freedom Network's Paul & Sheila Wellstone Award. De Baca graduated from Iowa State University and holds a J.D. from Michigan Law School.